5:
My company might just get bought
out entirely!
9:
B-by the same people who have
been chasing you all this time?
12:
One of the particularly persistent
groups, yes.
15:
Their CEO is an old buddy of mine,
back from when I was a
troubleshooter.
24:
Even when facing down old allies,
my new friends have my back. I love
it!
27: ...Alk, Stella. I can count on you, right?
33:
Been a while, Tritoma! Looks like
you've been doing all right for
yourself.
36:
...Yeah. Looks like you're still
gallivanting around, doing whatever
you please.
37:
Takes me back to our
troubleshooting days. Try as I might,
I could never keep you from running
recklessly off on your own...
40:
You've been pretty aggressive about
taking over my company, haven't
you?
43:
We're not forcing you to do
anything, and the contract is
flawless. I learned a lot from your
bad example, you see.
44:
I guess you were never able to
overcome your financial struggles,
huh? You would have been fine with
AltMeme's help...
46:
...Only a matter of time before you
rob your affiliates blind of all their
patents. The employees will be on
the street next, right?
49:
Relax. Unlike you, we treat each and
every one of our employees with the
utmost care.
50:
...And we will treat you the same.
This time around, you'll stay right by
my side—
53:
Okay, Tritoma. I'll leave CI in your
capable hands, then.
58:
All of my employees are convinced
that your company is as solid as it
gets. We've got nothing to worry
about.
60: I'll be bowing out myself, though.
64:
Thanks again, Tritoma. I think we
had this little meeting at the perfect
time.
67:
Heh-heh, maybe I should start my
next venture with you two!
70:
Catch you later, Tritoma. I wish you
nothing but success!
85:
Heh, you never give up. What did
you say earlier about learning from
my bad example?
87:
...Why won't you come back to
AltMeme? How could you just
abandon your employees like that?
88:
Why take the risks? We could have
grown our company with AltMeme
so easily!
90:
...Come back to me, Quinvere... Or
else!
93:
No thanks. I've taken quite a liking to
these two, you see.
96:
...Quinvere. Do you have ANY idea
how many people in Qualia City
have disappeared by going against
the grain?!
97:
Do you STILL not understand how I
feel?! All the things that should be
important to you... You'll drop it all
on a whim and never look back!
99:
Don't think that she'll treat you two
any different! Someday, she'll toss
you aside and never think of you
again!
103:
We're together now. All of us in this
moment.
108:
I like you, Tritoma. I always have,
and I always will.
111:
Even still, I have to keep going. If you
tell me to stay put, you can be sure
that it won't be long before I've left
you again.
116:
Maybe this is selfish, but I'm always
feeling abandoned too, you know?
119:
But either way, I have to keep
moving. No matter what, I won't give
this up.
122:
So do whatever you'd like. If you
want to keep coming after me, I
won't stop putting up a fight!
125:
But... Why are you so motivated
about this? Is this all you want?
127:
Just give it to me straight,. After all,
Tritoma... I—
132:
I always HATED that about you! You
never paid any attention at all to my
own fears and uncertainties!
133:
With you, Quinvere... More than
anything! I—
136:
All that hatred, envy, fear... Give me
everything you've got. It's all
beautiful to me.
138:
...Come here, Tritoma. Let's have all
kinds of new experiences together.
141:
...Awful... You're so awful! S-selfish, all
the time! Y-you...
147:
Everything worked out perfectly in
the end!
151:
So... The takeover's not going
through?
155:
That's right. I've partnered with
Tritoma's company and got them
out of AltMeme.
157:
I also heard from several
companies in Noxel Group, saying
they want to become independent!
I'll begin consultations soon!
164:
Sorry to drag you guys into this. I
figured I'd have to take some drastic
steps in order to get through to her.
167:
Oh, don't worry about it too much. If
we helped you two get on good
terms again...
172:
...You're still heading CI, but there's a
possibility that you'll let it go
someday, right?
175:
That's right. I might have to leave it
all behind one day, or I might stay
with it forever.
177:
Either way, I'll do anything to set a
new high score in life!
181:
...Yeah, I still don't really get what
you mean with that...
184: You don't? Want a lesson, then?
186:
I can give you an example relating
to love, right here and now.
193: Oh, that's too bad. Hm, in that case...
197:
Hey, Stella! Can I sleep in your bed
tonight?
201:
...Okay, seriously. Could you please
cut that out?
